UPDATE companies SET agent_ids_notes = 'Analysis by dev - 2026-02-04: ### Company Snapshot Problem & solution Soulside Al offers an Integrated AI platform for High-Acuity Behavioral Healthcare to automate compliance and documentation, addressing workforce strain (clinician turnover, documentation time) and rising claim denials/regulatory pressure. Key product claims include automated documentation and audit workflows, a FineTuning Engine for rapid payer requirement updates, and a voiceprint-based Group AI. Outcomes cited: reduce documentation time by ~80%, lower claim denials by up to 25%, faster claim submission (4 days vs 22), and avoidance of clawbacks. Ideal customer profile and pricing Target market: Moderate‑high acuity Behavioral Health (including mental health, substance use, eating disorders), with multi-location facilities. Immediate market sizing highlights in the deck point to ~35K facilities as the addressable base. Pricing signals include: ACV pricing ranges around $85–$250 per license per month; additional pricing cues show per-intervention pricing and multi‑product potential (documentation and compliance). Immediate SAM ~ $27B; SOM in the 10–15% range within the near term (3–4B) per the provided sizing slides; TAM cited as $240B with a longer‑term SAM ~ $150B. Status of product & traction highlight Live revenue as of Jan 2026 with ongoing pilots; notable milestones include: - Feb 2025: first revenue; Jul 2025: second customer; Oct–Nov 2025: one customer per week; Dec 2025: >$500K ARR; Jan 2026: live...' WHERE id = 443 AND (agent_ids_notes IS NULL OR agent_ids_notes = '');
